Example 18: SQS via random sampling for MAPbI3-MAPbBr3 (MA as parent molecule)
===============================================================================

Physical system
---------------
MAPbI3-MAPbBr3 mixed-halide perovskites tune the optical band gap continuously
by mixing I and Br on the X-site, with applications in photovoltaics and LEDs.
At the equimolar composition (x=0.5, MAPbI1.5Br1.5) the number of halide
arrangements in a 4x4x4 supercell is C(192,96) ~ 10^57, far beyond enumeration.
This example demonstrates the random-sampling + SQS workflow for this regime.

Workflow
--------
1. sod_random.sh -nconf 50000 -sym on
   randomsod draws 50,000 uniform random configurations of 96 Br in 192 halide
   sites, reduced under Pm-3m symmetry (EQMATRIX required). Results are written
   to n096/random/ENSEMBLE.

2. sod_sqs.sh (run from n096/random/)
   sqssod scores each configuration against the ideal random alloy using the van
   de Walle criterion (4th-order clusters, cutoff radii 12/8/8 A, omega=10).
   Rankings are written to n096/random/OUTSQS. The top-ranked configuration is
   c04258 (AbsErr ~ 0.0155).

3. genersod (run from n096/random/)
   Materialises the best SQS as a VASP POSCAR in n096/random/c04258/POSCAR
   (FILER=11, 768 atoms: 64 C + 64 N + 384 H + 64 Pb + 96 Br + 96 I).

@MA as parent molecule
----------------------
Unlike example08 (where MA substitutes for Cs on a fraction of A-sites), here
MA is the parent-structure species: every A-site is occupied by MA throughout.
The @MA prefix in the INSOD symbol list declares a parent molecule:

    # symbol(1:nsp): Atom symbols
    @MA Pb I

combsod and randomsod treat @MA as a spherical point species obeying Pm-3m site
symmetry; the symmetry analysis and random sampling act on the ideal lattice.
genersod then expands each A-site placeholder into a full MA molecule (MA.xyz,
8 atoms: C N 6H) with an independent random orientation (Shoemake uniform
quaternion sampling).

For SQS on a fully enumerated ensemble, see example16.

Files
-----
  INSOD                      SOD input (4x4x4 supercell, nsubs=96, FILER=11 VASP)
  SGO                        Symmetry operators for Pm-3m (space group 221)
  OPERATORS                  Operator list
  EQMATRIX                   Equivalence matrix (required for -sym on)
  supercell.cif              Reference placeholder geometry (CIF, P1)
  MA.xyz                     Methylammonium geometry (DFT-PBE optimised, Angstrom)
  n096/random/ENSEMBLE       50,000 symmetry-reduced random configurations
  n096/random/INSQS          SQS scoring parameters (4th-order, cutoffs 12/8/8 A)
  n096/random/OUTSQS         SQS scores and ranking for all 50,000 configurations
  n096/random/c04258/POSCAR  Best-SQS VASP POSCAR (768 atoms)

How to run
----------
1. Generate the random ensemble (from the example18/ directory):
     sod_random.sh -nconf 50000 -sym on

2. Score and rank:
     cd n096/random
     sod_sqs.sh

3. Write the best SQS structure:
     genersod

Supply INCAR, KPOINTS and POTCAR before running VASP. For other compositions
(different x), adjust nsubs in INSOD and regenerate the random ensemble.

Expected output
---------------
50,000 symmetry-reduced configurations in n096/random/ENSEMBLE.
OUTSQS rank 1: configuration c04258, AbsErr ~ 1.55e-02.
POSCAR: 768 atoms (64 MA molecules + 64 Pb + 96 I + 96 Br).
MA orientations are random and differ between genersod runs.
